  <%= link_to "#date_information", data: { toggle: "modal" } do %>
    <h4>Document Dates</h4>
  <% end %>

  <ul style="padding:0px;margin-left:15px;">
    <li>
      Found
      <%= time_tag @document.created_at %>
    </li>
    <li>
      Updated
      <%= time_tag @document.updated_at %>
    </li>
    <li>
      Relevant
      <% if @document.likely_date.nil? %>
        unknown
      <% end %>
      <%= time_tag @document.likely_date unless @document.likely_date.nil? %>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr>




  <div id="date_information" class="modal hide fade">
    <div class="modal-header">
      <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
      <h3>Date Information</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-body">
      <h4>Found Date</h4>
  <p>The date that Public Post first indexed this document from the town website.</p>

  <h4>Updated Date</h4>
  <p>The last time Public Post re-indexed this document from the town website. If you suspect a document has changed, check the town website as that is the official source of town documents.</p>

  <h4>Relevant Date</h4>
  <p>This is the Public Post's best guess at the most relevant date in the document. For example, if these are Meeting Minutes the Relevant Date is hopefully the date of the meeting. This is determined by an algorithm and it is imperfect at best.</p>

  <p>If you notice a mistake, you can create an account on the Post and edit the Relevant Date and other details. <%= link_to "Create your account", new_user_registration_path  %> and <%= link_to "Sign In", new_user_session_path %> to edit the Post and create email alerts.</p>

  <p><small><i>Please note: this does not, and cannot, change the original document at the town's website. User edits on this site update only the Public Post index. As always, the official sources of the documents in this index are the Vermont city and town websites: visit the town website for questions about the contents of any document or to ensure you have the truly latest version.</i></small></p>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-footer">
      <!-- <a href="#" class="btn">Close</a>
      <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Save changes</a> -->
    </div>
  </div>
